article.description: Bryant Horn rushed for 148 yards and a touchdown and Roc Thomas 105 yards and a score to lead Jacksonville State to a 36-6 win over Tennessee State on Thursday night in a regular-season finale.
article.headline: Jacksonville State completes perfect conference run, 36-6
article.linkText: Jacksonville State completes perfect conference run, 36-6
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. -- Bryant Horn rushed for 148 yards and a touchdown and Roc Thomas 105 yards and a score to lead Jacksonville State to a 36-6 win over Tennessee State on Thursday night in a regular-season finale. The Gamecocks (10-1, 8-0), who clinched their fourth straight Ohio Valley Conference title last week, now prepare of the FCS playoffs where they will be a high seed. The field will be announced on Sunday. Horn also threw for 115 yards and another score, a 45-yard pass to Austin Cummins, for a 10-0 halftime lead. Thomas ran 50 yards for a touchdown and Horn added a 44-yarder for a 24-0 lead in the third quarter. Cade Stinnett added a pair field goals, Jonathan Hagler sacked Michael Hughes for a safety and Tramel Terry ran 8 yards for a TD for the Gamecocks, who outgained Tennessee State 493-97. The Tigers (6-5, 2-5), who came in on a two-game win streak, scored their only touchdown on Hughes' 27-yard pass to Chris Rowland. Jacksonville State has won 32 consecutive conference games, the longest active streak in Division I. -- More AP college football: http://collegefootball.ap.org and http://www.twitter.com/AP-Top25
